    <p>This is not science fiction at Loft — Loft has a dedicated AI-for-Space business unit. The practical near-term applications are: automated anomaly detection (ML models trained on historical telemetry detect anomalies before they cascade), automated pass scheduling (optimisation algorithms allocate ground station contacts across the fleet), predictive maintenance (degradation models predict component failures before they occur), and adaptive payload scheduling (ML-driven allocation of payload operating time to maximise customer mission objectives given the power and thermal constraints).</p>

